---
import Container from "@/components/container";
import Layout from "./layout.astro";
---

<Layout subtitle="Privacy Policy">
    <section class="grid place-content-center">
        <Container
            className="max-w-xl p-6 dark:bg-neutral-900 dark:border-neutral-700"
        >
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">
                Privacy Policy
                <p class="text-xs font-medium">Effective date: 16.06.2025</p>
            </h1>

            <p>
                Welcome to openshorts ("we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy
                Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect your
                information when you visit or use our website. By accessing or
                using openshorts.dev, you agree to this policy.
            </p>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    <strong>Account Data:</strong> When you log in via GitHub or
                    Google OAuth, we collect your name, email, and avatar.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect device info (such as
                    IP, browser, operating system), pages viewed, interactions (likes,
                    comments), and AI Search prompts.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Cookies & Similar Technologies:</strong> We and third-party
                    services (like Google AdSense) use cookies and similar technologies
                    to collect usage data and serve personalized ads.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    To provide, maintain, and improve our features (e.g.,
                    account access, AI Search).
                </li>
                <li>
                    To personalize your experience and show relevant ads via
                    Google AdSense.
                </li>
                <li>To analyze website use and diagnose technical issues.</li>
                <li>
                    To enforce our Terms of Service and comply with legal
                    requests.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">3. Cookies & Advertising</h2>
            <p>
                We use cookies and third-party cookies for advertising purposes:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    Google (and other ad networks) uses cookies to serve
                    personalized ads based on your visits to our site or others.
                </li>
                <li>
                    You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a
                        href="https://adssettings.google.com">Ads Settings</a
                    > or <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices"
                        >aboutads.info</a
                    >
                </li>
                <li>
                    If you’re in the EU/EEA/UK, we obtain your explicit consent
                    before activating non-essential cookies (including AdSense).
                    You may revoke consent at any time.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">
                4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)
            </h2>
            <p>
                For EU/EEA/UK visitors, data processing relies on your
                consent—especially for personalized advertising and cookies. You
                may withdraw consent at any time.
            </p>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">5. Sharing Your Information</h2>
            <p>We may share your data:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    With Google as an independent data controller for AdSense
                    advertising.
                </li>
                <li>
                    With service providers and analytics tools to maintain and
                    improve the site.
                </li>
                <li>
                    To comply with legal obligations (e.g. in response to lawful
                    requests).
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">6. Data Security</h2>
            <p>
                We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to
                protect your data. However, no system is foolproof, and we
                cannot guarantee full security.
            </p>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">7. Your Rights</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Access, correct, update, or delete your personal data.</li>
                <li>Object to or restrict processing of your data.</li>
                <li>
                    Withdraw consent for cookies or personalized ads at any
                    time.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                We do not knowingly collect personal data from anyone under 13.
                If we learn we have, we will delete it promptly.
            </p>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this policy at any time. When changes occur, we
                post the new version with an updated effective date.
            </p>

            <h2 class="font-semibold mt-6">10. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have questions or want to exercise your rights, contact
                us at <a href="mailto:floyarehooked@gmail.com"
                    >floyarehooked@gmail.com</a
                >.
            </p>
        </Container>
    </section>
</Layout>
